 theme is addressed across a range of artistic and intellectual contexts, from Victorian neo-feudalism to socialism and the Arts and Crafts Movement, and drawing from work in literature, architecture, anthropology, political theory, law, art history and translation. Together with an analysis of the roots and legacy of Morris's work, the book offers a detailed survey of his many projects. Dr MARCUS WAITHE lectures in Victorian Literature at the University of Sheffield.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aArts, Englishy19th century. 0aHospitalityxPhilosophy. 0aMedievalismxHistoryy19th centuryzGreat Britain. 0aMedievalismzGreat BritainxHistoryy19th century. 0aUtopian socialism. 4aEnglish & American Literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh  aVictorian medievalism.  aWilliam Morris.  ahospitality.  autopia.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013z978311143139040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781846155123?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781846155123423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781846155123/original  a978-3-11-143139-0  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013b2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles